# defining calculateDF method
def calculateDF(tokenizedDocList: list):
    invInd = {}
    index = -1
    for doc in tokenizedDocList:
        index += 1
        for word in list(set(doc)):
            word = (word.lower()).translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation))
            if word in invInd:
                currdF = invInd[word]
                currdF += 1
                invInd[word] = currdF
            else: 
                invInd[word] = 1
    return invInd
In [9]:
# defining inverted index method
def makeInvInd(tokenizedDocList: list): 
    invInd = {} 
    index = -1 
    
    #N is the number of docs 
    N = len(tokenizedDocList) 
    dfIndex = calculateDF(tokenizedDocList) 
    for doc in tokenizedDocList: 
        index += 1 
        for word in list(set(doc)): 
            word = (word.lower()).translate(str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation)) 
            
            #tf = frequency in the document / len of doc  
            tf = doc.count(word) 
            df = dfIndex[word] 
            idf = np.log(N/(df)) 
            tfidf = (tf*idf) 
            if word in invInd: 
                currList = invInd[word] 
                currList.append((str(index), tfidf)) 
                invInd[word] = currList 
            else: 
                invInd[word] = [(str(index), tfidf)] 
    return invInd

#defining query vector method
def queryVector(docsList, query): 
    query = query.split() 
    queryInd = {} 
    dfIndex = calculateDF(docsList) 
    
    # idf = log(docs in corpus / docs with term in them) 
    N = len(docsList) 
    for term in query: 
        df = dfIndex[term] 
        idf = np.log(N/(df)) 
        if term in queryInd: 
            pass 
        else: 
            queryInd[term] = idf 
    return queryInd

#defining cosine method
def cosine(query, index): 
    scores = {} 
    
    for query_term, query_weight in query.items(): 
        for doc_id, doc_weight in index[query_term]: 
            if doc_id not in scores: 
                scores[doc_id] = query_weight * doc_weight 
            else: 
                scores[doc_id] += query_weight * doc_weight 
    
    finalScores = {} 
    
    for doc_id in scores.keys():
        finalScores[doc_id] = (float(scores[doc_id]) / (len(docsList[int(doc_id)])))
    
    return sorted(finalScores.items(), key = lambda x : x[1], reverse = True)
